Message from us
“Our mission at Barks and Brews Taphouse is to create a safe, welcoming environment where dogs can play off-leash while their owners enjoy craft beers, delicious wine, and great company, fostering connections within our community.”
Allen Bryant
Barks and Brews Taphouse
Welcome to Barks and Brews Taphouse, West Pinellas’ first “Off-Leash” Dog Park and Taphouse! We are thrilled to bring this fun offering to the communities of Largo, Seminole, Indian Rocks, St. Petersburg, and greater Pinellas County area.
Our 7000 SQ FT facility, with 1500 sq ft of indoor, climate-controlled space, is designed to offer a one-of-a-kind experience where dog lovers can enjoy a huge selection of craft beers and delicious wines while their furry friends play and socialize in a safe, off-leash environment. This dream was brought to life by three buddies who wanted a place in their neighborhood where both humans and dogs could connect and have fun.
We are excited to become a part of your community and provide a space that combines relaxation, socialization, and quality time with your pets. Stay tuned for more information and our official opening date. We can’t wait to welcome you and your canine companions to Barks and Brews Taphouse!
At Barks and Brews Taphouse, we believe that creating a space for dogs and their owners to connect is not just about fun, but a conscious decision to foster an environment where dog owners can spend time with their pets.
Origin Story
After years of grading essays and wrangling middle schoolers, Pat and Chris, two local teachers and passionate dog lovers, decided to trade textbooks for taps. Joining them by bringing his business experience, their friend Rian, helped turn the project into a reality. Combining their love for pups, people, and a good brew, they embarked on a new adventure: opening “Barks and Brews”. Pat, Chris and Rian are excited to create a welcoming space where dog owners can unwind with a cold beer while their furry friends socialize and make new tail-wagging buddies. And with more than 20 taps, you are bound to find something to enjoy. Not a huge dog person? No problem! Our bar area is dog free so come enjoy some great beer, great wine, and great company!!

What is Barks and Brews Taphouse?
kexworks
2024-07-03T14:19:09-04:00
What is Barks and Brews Taphouse?
Barks and Brews Taphouse is a unique, dog-friendly venue where you can enjoy a wide selection of craft beers and delicious wine while your furry friend plays in a safe, off-leash environment. We aim to create a fun, welcoming space for both humans and dogs to relax and socialize.
Where are you located?
kexworks
2024-06-14T03:53:11-04:00
Where are you located?
We are located in
14219 Walsingham Rd, Largo, FL 33774
.
Why is Barks and Brews 21+
kexworks
2024-11-15T09:15:29-05:00
Why is Barks and Brews 21+
Like other true dog bars, we are an “Off-Leash” facility. This means that dogs are running around off of their leash, and it’s not a good idea to have children near the faces of dogs they do not know. Many bars are 21+, so for the safety of kids and dogs, this is the most appropriate policy.
Is there an admission fee?
kexworks
2024-06-14T03:53:28-04:00
Is there an admission fee?
Yes, we charge a small admission fee for dogs to access our off-leash play area. This fee helps us maintain the space and ensure a clean, safe environment for all our guests. Please see our pricing page for more details. Humans are always free.
Are there any rules for bringing my dog?
kexworks
2024-10-25T10:38:12-04:00
Are there any rules for bringing my dog?
Yes, for the safety and enjoyment of all our guests, we have a few rules:
Please help us keep everyone safe and healthy!
Veterinarian records showing proof of CURRENT Rabies, Bordetella, and Distemper vaccinations must be on file with us
for your pet(s) to access the facility. Our software makes it easy to keep your records up to date. Please upload your records Here prior to your first visit.
While our friendly staff oversees the park, your animals are your responsibility. You must monitor, clean up after, and care for your own dog(s). Please do not let them go unattended. You must clean up your own pup’s mess!
To help ensure safe play, all dogs must be spayed or neutered if over the age of 10 months. Puppies must also be at least 4 months old to play at Barks and Brews.
No personal toys will be allowed in the park. The Barks and Brews team provides fun toys for use in the park.
No food or drink may be brought into the park.
No smoking, electronic or otherwise, is allowed anywhere on the property.
Please keep barking to a minimum. Dogs who can’t control their bark will be asked to be removed from play until they settle down. We reserve the right to ask any dogs to leave at our sole discretion.
You must be at least 21 years old to enter.
While we love play time, any dogs showing aggressive behavior or excessive dominance must be removed from play until they settle down. Repeat offenders will be asked to leave.
To ensure a safe environment for all, only 2 dogs per person are allowed in at a time.
Only flat-buckle collars should be worn by dogs in the off-leash yard. Harness, prong, pinch, choke and electric collars are not allowed in the park.
Can I bring more than one dog?
kexworks
2024-07-03T14:17:03-04:00
Can I bring more than one dog?
Yes, we allow two dogs per person. Each dog will need to have a separate admission fee paid, and the same rules apply to all dogs.
What kind of drinks do you offer?
kexworks
2024-06-06T21:55:44-04:00
What kind of drinks do you offer?
We offer a diverse menu of craft beers, wines, and non-alcoholic beverages. We also have special treats for your canine companions and small snacks for humans.
Do you host events?
kexworks
2024-05-25T00:14:45-04:00
Do you host events?
Yes, we regularly host a variety of events, including trivia nights, live music, and special dog-themed activities. Check our events calendar on our website for the latest updates and information.
Can I book a private event at Barks and Brews Taphouse?
kexworks
2024-05-25T00:15:13-04:00
Can I book a private event at Barks and Brews Taphouse?
Absolutely! We offer private event bookings for parties, corporate events, and other special occasions. Please contact us for more information on pricing and availability.
Do you have any membership options?
kexworks
2024-05-25T00:15:45-04:00
Do you have any membership options?
Yes, we offer membership packages that provide benefits such as discounted admission fees, special event access, and more. Visit our membership page for details.
What safety measures are in place?
kexworks
2024-05-25T00:16:03-04:00
What safety measures are in place?
The safety of our guests is our top priority. We maintain a clean and secure environment, with staff members on hand to monitor the play area and assist as needed. We also follow all local health and safety regulations.
How can I contact Barks and Brews Taphouse?
kexworks
2024-05-25T00:16:24-04:00
How can I contact Barks and Brews Taphouse?
You can reach us by phone, email, or through the contact form on our website. We also encourage you to follow us on social media for the latest news and updates.

Dog Park Rules
1. Please help us keep everyone safe and healthy! Veterinarian records showing proof of CURRENT Rabies, Bordetella, and Distemper vaccinations must be on file with us for your pet(s) to access the facility. Our software makes it easy to keep your records up to date. Please upload your records Here prior to your first visit.
2. While our friendly staff oversees the park, your animals are your responsibility. You must monitor, clean up after, and care for your own dog(s). Please do not let them go unattended.
You must clean up your own pup’s mess!
3. To help ensure safe play, all dogs must be spayed or neutered if over the age of 10 months. Puppies must also be at least 4 months old to play at Barks and Brews.
4. No personal toys will be allowed in the park. The Barks and Brews team provides fun toys for use in the park.
5. No food or drink may be brought into the park.
6. No smoking, electronic or otherwise, is allowed anywhere on the property.
7. Please keep barking to a minimum. Dogs who can’t control their bark will be asked to be removed from play until they settle down. We reserve the right to ask any dogs to leave at our sole discretion.
8. You must be at least 21 years old to enter.
9. While we love play time, any dog showing aggressive behavior or excessive dominance must be removed from play until they settle down. It is the responsibility of the “Pup-Parent” to ensure their dog is not harassing another dog. Repeat offenders will be asked to leave.
10. To ensure a safe environment for all, only 2 dogs per person are allowed in at a time.
11. Flat-buckle collars are preferred for dogs in the off-leash yard. Prong, pinch, choke and electric stimulation collars are not allowed in the park.
